      "description": "This 2004 BMW M3 (E46) represents a benchmark in naturally aspirated engineering. Power is delivered via the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six, featuring individual throttle bodies and dual-VANOS variable valve timing, all mated to a precise Getrag 6-speed manual transmission. This specimen features a factory-original limited-slip differential and has undergone a proactive subframe reinforcement to ensure structural integrity. The suspension retains its factory geometry with refreshed bushings and Bilstein dampers, providing the telepathic steering response these chassis are known for. Meticulously maintained with a documented service history, the paint is flawless, and the interior shows zero bolster wear. A true turn-key investment for the discerning purist.",
